\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces Backbone capacity and spatial dimensionality ablation on D-Brain with Rician noise $\sigma =0.1$ and $K=16$. All backbones use the same Hybrid RGS sampling and masked self-supervised loss. Plain-CNN-2D and Res-CNN-2D are lightweight generic CNNs, not architectural ports of the 3D backbones, so their comparison confounds dimensionality with architectural family and capacity. Restormer-2D is a capacity-matched, same-family 2D port of Restormer-hybrid-RGS, isolating spatial dimensionality as the sole factor within that family. Bold marks the best value per metric within each backbone family (DRCNet: 2 rows; Restormer: 3 rows).}}{29}{table.4}\protected@file@percent }
