\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {8}{\ignorespaces Main quantitative comparison on D-Brain with Rician noise $\sigma =0.1$. All Hybrid RGS methods use the fixed $K=16$ cross-model operating point. ROI metrics are computed over brain tissue only ($\Omega _{\mathrm  {ROI}}^{\mathrm  {eval}}$). Time/vol.\ is inference time per target diffusion volume when available. Bold values indicate the best self-supervised neural or regression result in each metric column; italicized rows are supervised reference runs using the same architecture and training protocol but with clean phantom targets (not rigorously tuned upper bounds).}}{38}{table.8}\protected@file@percent }
